Report with Rmarkdown
Report data analysis with Rmarkdown authoring framework

R4Archaeologists

Authoring framework (10 min)

Rmarkdown is an authoring framework for data science1 combining:

  • YAML header

  • code (R code)

  • narrative text (Markdown syntax).

Theory (30 min)

knitr package

Writing

Markdown syntax

Markdown syntax is plain text used in:

  • GitHub
  • Sketchfab
  • Slack
  • bookdown
    • Hinz (2021) R handbook
  • etc.

Markdown supports HTML:

  • Big font
  • bolded
  • etc.

Editing in RStudio, supports:

  • BibTex objects:

  • 3D objects
  • videos
  • etc.

Export Rmarkdown in:

  • HTML
    • this Rmarkdown document/webpage
  • PDF
  • LaTex
  • etc.

Rstudio environment

  • Navigate through the whole structure (bandeau)
  • Go to the previous/next section/code chunk (up/down arrows)
  • Insert a new code chunk

Rmarkdown structure

Code chunks

  • header
    • include
    • echo
    • eval
    • caption
    • etc.
  • body
    • R code

Narrative text

Markdown syntax

  • bold, italic, code, color
  • comments ‘>’
  • hyperlinks
  • bookmarks
  • lists
  • dataframe
  • footnotes2
  • calls
    • variable: ‘my.sum = 2’
    • chunk
    • figure
  • etc.

YAML header

  • author

  • date:

    • “03/02/22”
    • “3rd February 2022”
    • “22 January 2022”

  • table of contents (toc)

  • bibliographic references

Publishing

PDF, HTML, etc. Rpubs
